      <h2 style="text-align: center;">Volunteer From Home</h2>
      <p>
          Volunteering from home with the Turtle Shelter Project is an incredible way to make a difference from the comfort of your own space! 
          There are numerous steps in our vest production process, and each one is critical to ensuring we can provide quality products to those in need. 
          Whether you're a skilled sewer or have never threaded a needle, there's a place for you:
      </p>
      <ul>
          <li><strong>Cutting and Pinning:</strong> No sewing skills? No problem! You can help cut fabric pieces and pin them together.</li>
          <li><strong>Marking Components:</strong> Assist in ensuring vest components are prepared for sewing by marking and organizing pieces.</li>
          <li><strong>Basic Sewing:</strong> If you know how to sew a straight stitch, your contribution can help assemble crucial pieces of the vest.</li>
          <li><strong>Advanced Sewing:</strong> Confident with challenging sewing tasks? Your expertise will play a vital role in completing the most intricate parts of the vests.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
          This is your chance to make a meaningful impact from wherever you are. Share your time and talent to create high-quality vests that will make a real difference in someone’s life.
      </p>
      <h3>Contact Us</h3>
      <p>
          To volunteer from home, please email us with the following information:
          <ul>
              <li>Your <strong>first and last name</strong></li>
              <li>Your <strong>email</strong> and <strong>phone number</strong></li>
              <li>Your <strong>home address</strong></li>
              <li>Your <strong>availability</strong> (days and hours per month you can commit)</li>
              <li>Your <strong>sewing skill level</strong> (No Sewing, Beginner, Basic, Advanced)</li>
          </ul>
          Let us know how you'd like to help, and we’ll guide you through the process!
      </p>
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
          <a href="mailto:turtleshelterproject@gmail.com" class="button">Contact Us to Volunteer</a>
